<br>
I was browsing old screen shots last night when I saw chat with Boudreaux. The first time I met him was in CC while I was pharming silks for potions. He asked me to group with him to see if he would get XP with me at his current level. I said fine, DBed, and invited him. After a few tries I told him he was too low. He asked me about my bow, if I would sell it. I said no, not interested. A few days after that he asked me to make something for him in the pottery wheel in Thurgadin. I did.<br>
<br>
The screenshot in my EQ files took place a few days after Thurgadin. I was in EW grouped with Arimus who was helping me with the ring quest. We aggro'd a griffon and killed it. In /ooc I said, &quot;Griffon egg at (LOC).&quot; A druid offered to pay 400pp for looting rights. I thought, sweet deal. I wouldn't have placed a price on it but if someone offers, why not? Planning to divvy the money with Arimus, I kneeled on the bird. Boudreaux ran up, who happened to be in this druid's guild at the time. I mistakenly thought they were making an arrangement on the egg, and when I asked, he said he didn't know who this druid was. I assume you can't stay kneeled forever on a mob (I'm not important enough to lock mobs =P), and had to kneel again. Still waiting on the druid to arrive, who told me in /tell that she had to kill something she aggro'd, I had to kneel a third time when Boudreaux beat me too it and looted the egg WITHOUT my permission.<br>
<br>
&quot;Apparently&quot; he didn't know I was holding it down for someone else. (Yeah...I just like chaffing my knees while time idles by.) How he picked up on the egg at the location but missed the druid offering a sum of money for looting rights is beyond me. Sound familiar? My only regret is listening to Arimus and not shifting into psycho-mode.<br>
